<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1198,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Description.</emphasis>
Male: body length 7.8– 
<quantity box="[579,660,1199,1223]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
; width at humeri 1.7–2.2 mm. Body metallic blue in general; head slightly green; antennae purple brown or castaneous with segments I–II metallic; pronotum green blue; elytra cobalt blue; ventral surfaces dark blue, abdomen tinged with green; fore and middle legs pitchy red-brown with a purple tinge, hind femora blue-black and hind tibiae blue-purple with a pitchy tinge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Body largely covered with erect pale brown to silver hairs. Pronotum with dense silver pubescence laterally at apical and basal margins (
<figureCitation box="[452,556,1378,1403]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,931,954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,910]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,911]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Epania gressitti sp. nov. 1. holotype male; 2. paratype male. a. dorsal view; b. ventral view. Scale bars equal 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224909/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Figs 
<number box="[512,556,1379,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
a); scutellum with dense silver pubescence; elytra with some distinctly paler hairs along suture posterior to scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[637,709,1414,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 4. scutellum and adjacent elytra surface; 5. metathorax, ventral view; 6. mesothorax and metathorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224911/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[692,709,1415,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); mesepisternum and mesepimeron with dense brown to silver hairs, metathorax with dense silver pubescence at sides of anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1103,1450,1475]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 4. scutellum and adjacent elytra surface; 5. metathorax, ventral view; 6. mesothorax and metathorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224911/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[1087,1103,1450,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); metepisternum with sparse silver pubescence at margin; metepimeron with dense silver pubescence; hind coxae with dense silver pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1522,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1453,1476]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,151,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 4. scutellum and adjacent elytra surface; 5. metathorax, ventral view; 6. mesothorax and metathorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224911/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,227,1522,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); abdominal segments II and III with a band of silver pubescence, segment IV with sparse silver pubescence at the side (
<figureCitation box="[280,348,1558,1583]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1029,1052]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,219,989]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,219,990]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 9. Abdomen in Epania gressitti sp. nov., lateral view. 7. paratype male; 8 – 9. paratype female. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224912/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,348,1559,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Head not as broad as prothorax, with dense and deep punctures; frons flat and grossly punctate, constricted by eyes (
<figureCitation box="[217,301,1630,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 10. frons; 11. pronotum, dorsal view; 12. head and prothorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224913/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[270,301,1631,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennae 1.5–1.97 times as long as body, scape and shiny about as long as segment III with some deep punctures; pedicel shiny; segment IV longer than III, V subequal to VI–X, XI longest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Pronotum slightly longer than broad, broadest just behind middle, strongly and suddenly constricted near base, gradually and slightly narrowed towards apex, constricted above a short distance from apex; disc grossly and deeply reticulate-punctate, with punctures slightly smaller along median portion, apical and basal constricted portions largely impunctate (
<figureCitation box="[488,574,1810,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 10. frons; 11. pronotum, dorsal view; 12. head and prothorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224913/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[545,574,1811,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); prothorax raised at apex (
<figureCitation box="[904,992,1810,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1855,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1461,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Epania gressitti sp. nov. paratype male. 10. frons; 11. pronotum, dorsal view; 12. head and prothorax, lateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224913/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[961,992,1811,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Prosternal intercoxal process with a triangular (
<figureCitation box="[275,354,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,852,875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,831]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,832]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 14. Prosternal intercoxal process with a depression at apex in Epania gressitti sp. nov. 13. paratype male; 14. paratype female. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, fc = fore coxa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224914/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,354,1847,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
a) or an oval (
<figureCitation box="[511,590,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,852,875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,831]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,832]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 14. Prosternal intercoxal process with a depression at apex in Epania gressitti sp. nov. 13. paratype male; 14. paratype female. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, fc = fore coxa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224914/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,590,1846,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
b) depression at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" box="[199,885,1882,1907]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Scutellum slightly broader than long, subtruncate posteriorly.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1198,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Elytra reaching hind coxae, each elytron narrowed and unevenly rounded apically, more than 2.0 times as long as broad; disc coarsely punctate, with an oblique raised area on inner portion, separated from external portion and apex by an obliquely longitudinal depression; distal portion raised. Ventral surfaces sparsely punctate.</paragraph>
